1
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,520
Xiaolong isn't here?

2
00:01:57,600 --> 00:02:00,160
LINSHUI SECOND PRISON

3
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:02,920
Do you know yet?

4
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:04,840
In two months,

5
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:06,360
I can go home.

6
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:10,440
How are you doing in there?

7
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:11,840
All right.

8
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:13,400
Do you have any health problems?

9
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:15,040
No, I'm great.

10
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:20,040
I was so happy that I couldn't
sleep for the past two nights.

11
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:23,960
I've only had one thought
for the past few years.

12
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:25,640
That is, I will work hard.

13
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,280
I'll behave properly.

14
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,640
I'll aim for a reduced sentence.

15
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:31,120
I'll try to get home soon

16
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,360
and be with you all.

17
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:36,080
This day has finally come.

18
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:38,240
They shortened my
time by six months!

19
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:40,920
Isn't that great?

20
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:42,920
That's great.

21
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:44,640
I have it all figured out.

22
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:45,720
When I get home,

23
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:48,680
I'll tidy up our home.

24
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,880
Keep that sandy lot for me.

25
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:52,520
I'm going to plant watermelons.

26
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:55,200
We'll lease out the
rest of the land.

27
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:57,400
Xiaolong isn't young anymore.

28
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:58,960
To be honest, he
should get married.

29
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,440
When I get back,

30
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:03,560
I will renovate our
old house for him.

31
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,296
- It...
- I'll add another floor.

32
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:06,960
I already sold the house.

33
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,240
You sold the house?

34
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:13,640
Do you not live in
the village anymore?

35
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:14,720
Are you in the city?

36
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,720
That's good too!

37
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,000
I'll be fine.

38
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:20,360
I can do odd jobs
around the city.

39
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:22,400
If I'm lucky,

40
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:25,560
I'll get a job that provides
food and accommodation.

41
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,400
In the future,

42
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:29,640
you shouldn't look for us.

43
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,800
You…

44
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,440
Xiaolong has graduated.

45
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:37,280
He is staying in
Jialin for work.

46
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:41,080
We're moving to Jialin.

47
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,680
All these years,

48
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,880
because of you,

49
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,600
others have looked down on him.

50
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:58,000
He has suffered a lot.

51
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:01,240
People say that his
dad is a murderer.

52
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,360
In our hometown,

53
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:08,200
he can't make a living.

54
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:13,600
Who would want to marry him?

55
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,880
In the future,

56
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:22,280
you live your life.

57
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,760
We'll live our own lives.

58
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,360
Don't ever contact us again.

59
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:29,600
When you get out,

60
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:31,560
don't…

61
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:33,480
Don't look for us.

62
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,720
Okay.

63
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,440
I got it.

64
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,680
As long as you two are happy,

65
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:54,760
I'll be fine.

66
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:52,640
SEVERELY PUNISH EVIL,
GUARD THE PEACE OF JIALIN

67
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,080
Here, have some water.

68
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,120
- Thank you.
- Have a seat.

69
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:13,080
Thank you for coming here to
cooperate with our investigation.

70
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,920
No, it's something I should do.

71
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,560
It's such a serious matter.

72
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:19,400
We really want to be of help.

73
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:23,800
STAY TRUE TO YOUR ORIGINAL
ASPIRATIONS, REMEMBER THE MISSION

74
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:25,400
There were no
survivors on the bus.

75
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:29,800
We hope to learn what
happened on the bus

76
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:32,240
from passengers who got
off along the route.

77
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:36,360
We checked all the
CCTVs along the route.

78
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:40,920
You got off at the last stop
before the accident, right?

79
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,160
Yes, the Yanjiang
East Road stop.

80
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:46,160
We never expected it.

81
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:47,600
After we got off,

82
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:49,440
the bus exploded.

83
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,120
I remember seeing
the security footage.

84
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,480
Based on your behavior,

85
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,240
it seemed to be a
last-minute decision.

86
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,080
Here's the thing.

87
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,240
The other day,

88
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:05,440
my boyfriend lost a
backpack on the bus.

89
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:06,520
It was on this bus line.

90
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,920
When we got to the
Yanjiang East Road stop,

91
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,240
we saw a man outside

92
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:14,360
who had the exact same backpack.

93
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:16,320
We just wanted to
get off and ask him.

94
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:18,760
But it turned out not to be it.

95
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,680
Before he even got on,

96
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:24,520
you had noticed his backpack?

97
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,840
He was wearing his
backpack in the front.

98
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:30,360
That's why it was
rather obvious.

99
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:34,120
Why didn't you wait
until he got on the bus?

100
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:39,160
I guess we were
pretty impatient.

101
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:47,680
We talked to the guy
with the backpack.

102
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:49,800
He said you two pushed
him off the bus.

103
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,120
And then,

104
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:53,920
you unzipped his
backpack to check it.

105
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,480
Is that true?

106
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:01,120
I don't get it.

107
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:04,280
Whether your boyfriend's
bag was stolen or robbed,

108
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,280
so many days have
already passed.

109
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:08,400
The content would be long gone.

110
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:13,160
Why did you still unzip the bag?

111
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:14,240
What were you checking?

112
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:16,160
Can't you be certain

113
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:17,920
from the exterior?

114
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,680
This…

115
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,080
This…

116
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:25,520
We didn't think that far ahead.

117
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,360
When did you two…

118
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:34,159
find out about the incident?

119
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:38,640
The boy had a kitten in his bag.

120
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:40,320
The cat got out.

121
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:42,159
We had just found the cat

122
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:43,760
when we saw the explosion.

123
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,160
Were you surprised?

124
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,360
I was quite surprised
at the time.

125
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:00,560
If I hadn't gotten off
earlier, I would have…

126
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:02,600
Yes.

127
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,720
Which stop did you get on at?

128
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,640
Were you alone?

129
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,320
How long did you
stay on the bus?

130
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:13,760
I got on the bus
in Gaoxin District

131
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:15,320
and waited for my
girlfriend to board

132
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:17,640
at the University Town stop.

133
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:18,880
We stayed for over ten stops.

134
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,560
It took about an hour.

135
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:22,880
While on the bus,

136
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,960
aside from the
backpack you mentioned,

137
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:27,040
did you notice anyone unusual?

138
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:28,680
Anyone unusual?

139
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:31,160
Actually, there was.

140
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:33,760
There were two men who
were quite unusual.

141
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,520
One was an older man
who sat next to us.

142
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:39,640
<i>He was on his phone as soon as
he got on and looked sneaky.</i>

143
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,800
<i>There was a huge
case next to him.</i>

144
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:43,160
He touched it from time to time.

145
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:44,800
It was weird.

146
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,760
There was also an old
man who sat in the front.

147
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:47,840
He had a burlap bag.

148
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:49,840
<i>There seemed to be
watermelons in it.</i>

149
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,840
<i>But every time
someone passed by,</i>

150
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:53,200
he got so nervous.

151
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:55,720
It didn't seem normal.

152
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:14,920
It was this person.

153
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,320
Ma Guoqiang.

154
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:21,480
Why did you find him suspicious?

155
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:24,600
- Pull up his file.
- Got it.

156
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:28,320
Look at this.

157
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:35,200
- Here.
<i>- "If you smile, it returns the greeting."</i>

158
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:36,120
<i>As I always say,</i>

159
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,576
<i>blessings always
outnumber worries.</i>

160
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,480
<i>If you want happiness,
look for Mr. One.</i>

161
00:10:39,560 --> 00:10:40,560
<i>Yes!</i>

162
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:45,000
Even the comments say that this
old man's expression is scary.

163
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:48,080
After seeing this,

164
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:49,800
we remembered.

165
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:52,240
When he was on the bus,

166
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:55,160
he did seem nervous.

167
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:56,240
It was pretty weird.

168
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:03,720
The three of them are
saying the same thing.

169
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:04,960
It was a misunderstanding.

170
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:08,400
The other two seem to
be cooperative as well.

171
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,320
They told us everything
that they saw on the bus.

172
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:14,040
Aren't they a little
too cooperative?

173
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:17,880
Theoretically, they don't
know the actual situation.

174
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:19,760
They couldn't have
known about the bomb.

175
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:23,440
But they all happen
to suspect Ma Guoqiang

176
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:25,560
and the burlap bag at his feet.

177
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:27,320
But Mr. Zhang, we asked them

178
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:29,120
if there was anything
suspicious onboard.

179
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:31,560
If you were a
civilian on the bus,

180
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,120
would you notice these details?

181
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:35,720
Would you notice a burlap
bag at a farmer's feet?

182
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:37,160
Is that normal?

183
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:40,360
Some people
deliberately cater to us

184
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,760
when cooperating
with the police.

185
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:43,600
That's understandable.

186
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:45,920
Ms. Du, Mr. Zhang.

187
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,761
This is the information on the
passenger that the witnesses mentioned.

188
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:55,160
Ma Guoqiang. His
hometown is Ningxia.

189
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:57,560
In 2006,

190
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:59,920
he killed someone with a
three-wheeler and fled.

191
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,280
He spent four years on the run.

192
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,720
He was caught in 2010
and sentenced to 9 years.

193
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:05,840
He was released in early 2017.

194
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:07,640
He is now a farmer
in his hometown.

195
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:10,880
Ma Guoqiang arrived in
Jialin this morning on a bus.

196
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:13,160
Since his release, he has
been growing melons back home.

197
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,280
He lives alone.

198
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:16,560
His son and ex-wife
also live in Jialin.

199
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,120
His mental state is unknown.

200
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,480
He might have financial issues.

201
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:21,920
Is his family here?

202
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,920
Yes, we're filling them in now.

203
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,040
I think it's almost done.

204
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,320
Mr. Zhang.

205
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:28,920
- Check it out.
- Okay.

206
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,560
Do we release the
three young ones?

207
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:32,480
Release them.

208
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:34,096
- Have them keep their phones on.
- Okay.

209
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:35,200
Wait a minute.

210
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:38,240
I think Li Shiqing
can be released first.

211
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,160
Monitor her phone.

212
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:41,160
Find out what she's up
to after she leaves.

213
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:43,560
Keep these two for now.

214
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:45,920
After I meet with Ma
Guoqiang's family,

215
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,080
I want to talk to
those two again.

216
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:54,000
Something still doesn't
feel right to me.

217
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:03,000
Mr. Wang was such a nice person.

218
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:05,160
How could this happen?

219
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,320
Yes.

220
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,360
The main responsibility…

221
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:11,080
FUCHENG AMUSEMENT
PARK BUNGEE JUMP CLUB

222
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,800
MA XIAOLONG

223
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:38,960
When was the last
time you saw your dad?

224
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,320
He was visiting.

225
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:46,216
- Did he tell you?
- Mr. Zhang, it's these two.

226
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:48,080
Ma Guoqiang's ex-wife and son.

227
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,760
You didn't have
any contact at all?

228
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,200
Come on.

229
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,000
Mr. Zhang.

230
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:04,040
This is Liu Caicai,
Ma Guoqiang's ex-wife.

231
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:05,360
This is his son, Ma Xiaolong.

232
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:07,120
- Hello.
- My condolences.

233
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:13,800
Ma Xiaolong.

234
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:16,000
Can you come with me?

235
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:17,760
I have some things to ask you.

236
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,920
What is it, sir?

237
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,200
What is it?

238
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:23,680
Don't worry.

239
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:25,120
We just want to learn more.

240
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:26,960
It's nothing.

241
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,960
Mom, don't worry.

242
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:30,240
Don't worry.

243
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,320
Come on.

244
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:32,960
I'll be right back.

245
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:35,960
It's okay, ma'am.

246
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,800
We just have a few
simple questions.

247
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:39,520
Please have a seat.

248
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:44,560
Have a seat.

249
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:05,280
Let's go.

250
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,360
Your university is quite far.

251
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:14,880
Here's the thing, ma'am.

252
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,520
I want to refresh your memory.

253
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:18,320
When was the last time

254
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:19,680
you spoke to Ma Guoqiang?

255
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:22,840
I can't remember.

256
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,400
What's wrong?

257
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:28,840
Nothing.

258
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,560
Mr. Lu.

259
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:39,640
Go ahead.

260
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:42,320
I want to wait here
for my boyfriend.

261
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,360
We'll leave together
when he comes out.

262
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:46,560
You don't know how long
you will have to wait.

263
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:47,480
Let's go.

264
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:48,840
It's okay.

265
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:51,040
There are no buses
at this hour anyway.

266
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:53,160
I'll wait to take
a taxi with him.

267
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:54,880
Get back to work.

268
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:56,160
Okay, you can wait here.

269
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:57,240
Don't roam around.

270
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:10,960
Did you visit him
while he was in prison?

271
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:15,600
Once or twice a year.

