the explosion,

549
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:57,960
and rescuing passengers.

550
00:30:58,040 --> 00:30:59,680
Did those two tell you those?

551
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:01,400
We don't have much time left.

552
00:31:01,440 --> 00:31:02,600
Listen to me.

553
00:31:02,680 --> 00:31:04,960
Put together all the
information you have.

554
00:31:05,040 --> 00:31:06,640
Give it to me. I can use it.

555
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:08,480
I'm going to save
the world for you.

556
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:11,040
Save the world? Sure.

557
00:31:11,120 --> 00:31:12,360
We can also take part.

558
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:13,880
We'll help you save the world.

559
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:15,680
But you have to answer
our questions first.

560
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:17,160
I can't answer you right now.

561
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:18,560
There isn't much time left.

562
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:20,720
Lu Di, you don't have
to worry about that.

563
00:31:20,800 --> 00:31:22,240
We have plenty of time.

564
00:31:22,320 --> 00:31:24,440
We can all take turns
keeping you company.

565
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:26,880
Once midnight hits,
everything will reset.

566
00:31:27,440 --> 00:31:28,440
Hurry.

567
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:31,280
Trust me!

568
00:31:37,320 --> 00:31:38,320
Xiao Heyun.

569
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:40,240
- Do you know...
- That's enough.

570
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:43,800
I'll be honest and tell
the truth. How about that?

571
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:47,760
I am…

572
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:52,840
in a time loop.

573
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:58,856
You thought the explosion today
was caused by a car crash.

574
00:31:58,880 --> 00:32:01,520
But at night, you will
find a bomb on the bus.

575
00:32:02,640 --> 00:32:03,640
Right?

576
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:04,760
If I wasn't in a time loop,

577
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:06,160
how would I know that?

578
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:09,240
I don't have enough time.

579
00:32:09,320 --> 00:32:10,400
I have to go soon.

580
00:32:10,480 --> 00:32:11,840
If you have anything to tell me,

581
00:32:11,920 --> 00:32:12,760
tell me now.

582
00:32:12,840 --> 00:32:14,000
You should tell us the truth.

583
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:15,400
Xiao Heyun.

584
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:17,280
When did you start
planning all this?

585
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:30,960
It will be the 16th time soon.

586
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:50,880
ROUTE 45 TO XUEYE SOUTH ROAD

587
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:54,400
NEXT STOP, YANJIANG EAST ROAD

588
00:32:54,480 --> 00:32:59,120
KEEP CLEAR OF THE DOORS

589
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:01,920
DO NOT USE THIS AS SUPPORT

590
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:13,560
What happened?

591
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:15,920
Did you say something wrong
at the police station?

592
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:17,520
No.

593
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:21,480
Mr. Jiang said that Lu Di wrote
a suicide note for his mom.

594
00:33:21,560 --> 00:33:23,320
He wants to join the time loop.

595
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:26,920
What did you say?

596
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:28,000
I…

597
00:33:28,320 --> 00:33:29,840
It doesn't matter what I said.

598
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:32,840
Anyway, I don't want to go to the
police and talk about loops anymore.

599
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:33,920
I'm sick of it.

600
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:36,360
Me too.

601
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:42,560
I have a big clue.

602
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:46,800
That old man.

603
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:48,000
He has a criminal record.

604
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:49,400
He has a death on
his conscience.

605
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:52,920
As in, he has killed someone.

606
00:33:56,800 --> 00:33:59,120
He does have a weird bag.

607
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:00,800
Should we look into him?

608
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:06,200
I'll go and check it out first.

609
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:08,880
Be careful.

610
00:34:44,639 --> 00:34:46,639
He is so careful with that bag.

611
00:34:46,719 --> 00:34:47,920
There must be something.

612
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:59,080
WE ARE ARRIVING AT
YANJIANG EAST ROAD!

613
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:06,720
Don't we also have Lu Di?

614
00:35:09,280 --> 00:35:10,280
Yes.

615
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:35,440
YANJIANG EAST ROAD STOP

616
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:40,800
Care…

617
00:35:47,160 --> 00:35:48,400
Thank you.

618
00:35:49,520 --> 00:35:50,760
Are you okay?

619
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:55,120
<i>The bus is moving.
Please hold on tight.</i>

620
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:57,720
- <i>Next stop, Yanjiang West Road.</i>
- Excuse me. Let me go through.

621
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:01,440
Thank you.

622
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:07,920
He is not in the time loop.

623
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:11,360
Why don't we say the
secret code to him?

624
00:36:13,160 --> 00:36:14,480
Explaining it to him now

625
00:36:14,560 --> 00:36:15,920
would be such a waste of time.

626
00:36:17,120 --> 00:36:19,080
Let's stick to our plan for now.

627
00:36:19,600 --> 00:36:21,240
We'll call him if we need help.

628
00:36:23,080 --> 00:36:23,960
That's too bad.

629
00:36:24,040 --> 00:36:26,040
That's one less helper for us.

630
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:27,360
It's okay.

631
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:28,760
I've come up with a plan.

632
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,600
Do you know how to count?

633
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:37,880
This is clearly four stops.

634
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:39,160
How did you count?

635
00:36:39,240 --> 00:36:41,240
I counted by hand.
It's five stops.

636
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:43,200
Let's see how you count by hand.

637
00:36:43,280 --> 00:36:44,120
Look.

638
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:45,720
See for yourself. Isn't it…

639
00:36:46,240 --> 00:36:47,400
- What are you doing?
- Sorry.

640
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:48,760
I'm sorry.

641
00:36:50,400 --> 00:36:51,640
What are you doing?

642
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:53,016
- Why did you kick my melons?
- What?

643
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:53,880
No fighting!

644
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:55,360
No fighting! What are you doing?

645
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:56,840
It was him.

646
00:36:57,240 --> 00:36:58,600
He kicked my melons first.

647
00:36:58,680 --> 00:36:59,880
He ruined two of them.

648
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:01,400
I didn't mean to push him.

649
00:37:01,480 --> 00:37:02,680
I also didn't mean to.

650
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:03,840
You didn't mean to either?

651
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:06,040
The first time, fine.

652
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:07,800
But the second time?

653
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:09,560
- Exactly.
- I was watching.

654
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:10,680
You did it on purpose.

655
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:12,720
Tell us. Why did you
kick the watermelons?

656
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:14,400
Were your legs itching to do so?

657
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:15,880
You deserve that push.

658
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:19,000
- And you. Yes, you!
- Why did you…

659
00:37:19,560 --> 00:37:21,280
He kicked your melon,
so you pushed him?

660
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:23,120
You pushed so hard.
What if he got hurt?

661
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:26,400
- I'm sorry.
- Why are you apologizing to me?

662
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:28,200
You pushed him.
Say sorry to him.

663
00:37:28,280 --> 00:37:29,720
I'm sorry. Are you hurt?

664
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:31,840
Why should you apologize to him?

665
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:33,080
Don't be sorry.

666
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:34,600
He started it.

667
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:37,040
I don't mean to
criticize you, young man.

668
00:37:37,120 --> 00:37:39,520
But look at what you
did to his melons.

669
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:41,120
You should apologize!

670
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:42,080
Do I have to tell you?

671
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:43,160
- Yes.
- My goodness!

672
00:37:43,240 --> 00:37:44,360
It's okay.

673
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:46,680
I'm sorry for the trouble.

674
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:48,040
Yes, I'm sorry.

675
00:37:48,120 --> 00:37:50,040
It looks like you
still have a few…

676
00:37:51,400 --> 00:37:52,400
Don't push it.

677
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:53,520
I…

678
00:37:53,600 --> 00:37:54,600
Go back.

679
00:38:00,120 --> 00:38:01,640
Sir, I'm so sorry.

680
00:38:01,720 --> 00:38:04,120
My boyfriend was
fighting with me today.

681
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:05,600
He's not in a good mood.

682
00:38:05,680 --> 00:38:07,840
Is that any reason to take
it out on his watermelons?

683
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:09,680
Look what happened
to the watermelons.

684
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:11,880
It's such a waste
of good watermelons.

685
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:13,160
That's too bad.

686
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:15,040
How about this?

687
00:38:15,120 --> 00:38:16,960
I'll compensate you
for the watermelons.

688
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:23,760
My melons aren't for sale.

689
00:38:24,680 --> 00:38:27,320
I carried them a long way here.

690
00:38:28,680 --> 00:38:30,440
They are for my son.

691
00:38:57,360 --> 00:38:58,400
Sir.

692
00:38:58,880 --> 00:39:01,320
Are you Ma Xiaolong's dad?

693
00:39:03,640 --> 00:39:04,640
Who are you?

694
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:06,760
I also work at
Full House Realty.

695
00:39:06,840 --> 00:39:08,120
I'm his colleague.

696
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:09,360
Is it really you?

697
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:11,160
He showed me a picture of you.

698
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:13,080
Really?

699
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:17,080
Here.

700
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:22,480
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

701
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:24,080
Look, just now,

702
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:25,880
I really didn't
mean to push him.

703
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:28,640
Don't apologize.
He was the problem.

704
00:39:29,120 --> 00:39:30,800
- Have a seat.
- Okay.

705
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:32,960
Do you know each other?

706
00:39:33,680 --> 00:39:34,960
What a small world.

707
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:36,880
That's interesting.
What's going on?

708
00:39:36,960 --> 00:39:38,360
What is it?

709
00:39:39,920 --> 00:39:43,000
I haven't seen
Xiaolong in years.

710
00:39:43,520 --> 00:39:44,520
Fortunately,

711
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:47,000
he is connected with
relatives on WeChat Moments.

712
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:48,200
My friend told me.

713
00:39:48,680 --> 00:39:51,000
He posted something
in the last two days.

714
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:54,400
He said he wanted to eat
the watermelons I grew,

715
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:55,760
but he couldn't come home.

716
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:57,320
I thought that

717
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:59,360
I would bring him
the watermelons.

718
00:39:59,840 --> 00:40:01,160
Mostly,

719
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:02,920
I just want to see him.

720
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:05,080
Is it that hard for two
living people to meet?

721
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:07,520
You have no idea.

722
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:09,440
It's all my fault.

723
00:40:10,160 --> 00:40:11,360
We just can't meet.

724
00:40:13,160 --> 00:40:14,160
Sir.

725
00:40:14,840 --> 00:40:16,120
Xiaolong wants to see you too.

726
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:17,920
It's true.

727
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:20,000
Xiaolong always tells us.

728
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:22,240
He says his dad's
melons are the sweetest.

729
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:25,920
He even said he wanted to
visit you over the new year.

730
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:28,320
That's great.

731
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:31,960
Thank you so much for looking
after Xiaolong at work.

732
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:35,000
Ever since Xiaolong was little,

733
00:40:35,080 --> 00:40:37,520
he said he wanted to
grow up to have a job

734
00:40:38,400 --> 00:40:39,960
that required wearing a suit.

735
00:40:40,040 --> 00:40:41,600
He has such a job now.

736
00:40:41,680 --> 00:40:43,240
He also has such
a nice colleague.

737
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:45,520
I have to thank my ancestors.

738
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:48,040
Since you work with Xiaolong,

739
00:40:48,120 --> 00:40:50,120
I'll treat you to a watermelon.

740
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:51,880
When Xiaolong gets them,

741
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:53,760
he will share them with
his colleagues anyway.

742
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:00,800
It's too big.

743
00:41:00,880 --> 00:41:03,600
Even though this
watermelon is broken,

744
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:05,200
the flesh is clean.

745
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:07,320
- Here.
- Thank you.

746
00:41:07,920 --> 00:41:09,280
- Sir.
- Me too?

747
00:41:09,360 --> 00:41:11,640
- Yes.
- Wait, let me film this.

748
00:41:11,720 --> 00:41:12,600
Thank you so much.

749
00:41:12,680 --> 00:41:14,816
These are watermelons grown
in the sand in the northwest.

750
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:16,640
They are so sweet. You
won't find them here.

751
00:41:17,240 --> 00:41:18,680
- I'll have one.
- Everyone gets one.

752
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:19,800
Thank you.

753
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:20,880
It's so sweet.

754
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:23,000
No wonder Xiaolong
always talks about it.

755
00:41:24,400 --> 00:41:26,520
Miss, which stop are
you getting off at?

756
00:41:26,600 --> 00:41:28,400
Why don't I pick one for
you to take with you?

757
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:30,840
No, don't pick one.

758
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:32,600
The ones on the floor
are already a waste.

759
00:41:32,680 --> 00:41:34,280
Okay. Let's finish
it first, okay?

760
00:41:34,360 --> 00:41:35,840
It's so sweet.

761
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:36,920
It's delicious.

762
00:41:42,160 --> 00:41:43,320
This is good.

763
00:41:44,520 --> 00:41:45,680
Here. Have another piece.

764
00:41:50,160 --> 00:41:51,640
JIALIN RIVER-CROSSING
BRIDGE, 1,500 M

765
00:41:54,880 --> 00:41:56,680
Dad, they are eating watermelon.

766
00:42:00,640 --> 00:42:02,400
I want watermelon too.

767
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:03,480
I…

768
00:42:04,840 --> 00:42:05,920
How about grapes?

769
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,160
Your mom got you some grapes.

770
00:42:07,240 --> 00:42:08,280
Have some grapes.

771
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:10,640
No! I want watermelon.

772
00:42:10,720 --> 00:42:11,880
Listen to me.

773
00:42:12,440 --> 00:42:13,840
Grapes are the same
as watermelons.

774
00:42:13,880 --> 00:42:15,960
They both have seeds
and skin and are sweet.

775
00:42:16,040 --> 00:42:17,040
Have some grapes.

776
00:42:17,680 --> 00:42:19,560
No, buy me a watermelon.

777
00:42:20,120 --> 00:42:21,320
Do you want some water? Here.

778
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,400
Have some water.

779
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:24,120
I don't want water.
I want watermelon.

780
00:42:24,200 --> 00:42:25,240
It's up to you.

781
00:42:59,360 --> 00:43:01,560
Miss, there are more.

782
00:43:01,640 --> 00:43:03,280
Let's share them all.

783
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:08,480
What do you think?
Isn't it sweet?

784
00:43:17,640 --> 00:43:18,920
Sir.

785
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:21,080
Xiaolong said that he was sorry.

786
00:43:21,160 --> 00:43:22,520
He shouldn't have run away.

787
00:43:23,160 --> 00:43:24,920
He really loves you.

788
00:43:40,520 --> 00:43:41,840
I am not a celebrity.

789
00:43:41,920 --> 00:43:43,880
I'm just an ordinary
person like you.

790
00:43:44,600 --> 00:43:46,760
I was so moved by what
you guys did last night.

791
00:43:46,840 --> 00:43:48,080
It's true.

792
00:43:48,160 --> 00:43:49,496
Blessings always
outnumber worries.

793
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:50,440
If you want happiness,
look for Mr. One.

794
00:43:50,520 --> 00:43:51,520
As I always say,

795
00:43:51,600 --> 00:43:54,240
"If you don't abandon me, I
will stay with you for life."

796
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:02,440
I was also moved

797
00:44:02,520 --> 00:44:03,680
by what you said earlier.

798
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:10,760
I just feel bad
for that old man.

799
00:44:10,840 --> 00:44:12,840
He was so upset and sad.

800
00:44:12,920 --> 00:44:14,960
So I mentioned his son.

801
00:44:15,680 --> 00:44:17,560
I didn't expect it to go on.

802
00:44:19,280 --> 00:44:20,160
However,

803
00:44:20,240 --> 00:44:22,960
if I could give him some
comfort in his last moment,

804
00:44:23,040 --> 00:44:24,560
isn't that a good thing?

805
00:44:36,040 --> 00:44:37,040
There are two left.

806
00:44:44,040 --> 00:44:46,360
They even got on at
the same bus stop.

807
